title: Facebook Outperformance To Continue
text: I am back with a look at Facebook's Q4 and how it will shape Q1 earnings.

title: Facebook working on voice assistant technology that may rival Alexa, Siri: Sources
text: CNBC's Sal Rodriguez joins "Power Lunch" to discuss how Facebook is working on a voice assistant to rival the likes of Amazon's Alexa, Apple's Siri and the Google Assistant. The effort is coming out of the company's Facebook Reality Labs, a division that works on long-term tech projects and hardware, including the company's virtual reality Oculus headsets.

title: Facebook is working on a voice assistant to rival Amazon Alexa and Apple Siri
text: A team in Redmond, Washington, is working to build a competitor to Alexa, Siri, and the Google Assistant.

title: Facebook to Terminate P2P Services in UK and France
text: Facebook (FB) is likely to stop providing peer-to-peer (P2P) payment service on its Messenger platform in France and the U.K. from Jun 15, 2019.

title: Facebook (FB) Expected to Beat Earnings Estimates: What to Know Ahead of Q1 Release
